  "derivation": "CREATE2 per the factory's proxyOf: address = keccak256(0xff || factory || user-as-32-byte-salt || keccak256(creationCode || abi.encode(implementation, user)))[12..]. Every input is chain-free, so a generation's proxy for a user is the same address on every chain it is deployed to — the fixture intentionally carries no chain axis. The creation_code digests pin the embedded .bin blobs, which are byte-identical to the TypeScript arbiter's COW_SHED_PROXY_INIT_CODE constants. Rows marked with an anchor are the arbiter's own test vectors (external anchors that transitively prove the creation-code bytes and the formula); the remaining rows re-run the pinned formula over the pinned inputs for regression coverage. The custom-options anchor pairs the v1.0.0 creation code with a non-canonical factory and implementation, exercising the explicit init_code_hash + CREATE2 path.",
